<p><strong>The Darkest Hour by Maya Banks: A Comprehensive Guide</strong></p>
<p><strong>Q: What is "The Darkest Hour" by Maya Banks about?</strong></p>
<p>A: "The Darkest Hour" is a suspenseful and thrilling novel that follows the story of Morganna Crow, a Special Forces operative tasked with infiltrating a dangerous criminal organization to rescue a kidnapped senator. As she delves deeper into the underworld, Morganna faces deadly enemies, moral dilemmas, and a forbidden romance that could put everything at risk.</p>
<p><strong>Q: What is the main theme of the novel?</strong></p>
<p>A: The novel explores themes of love, betrayal, and the darkness that lurks within the human heart. Morganna's struggle to balance her mission with her growing connection to her target challenges her beliefs and forces her to confront the complexities of both good and evil.</p>
<p><strong>Q: Is "The Darkest Hour" a standalone novel?</strong></p>
<p>A: Yes, "The Darkest Hour" is a standalone novel and can be read without prior knowledge of other books. However, it is set in the same world as Banks' "Colton" series, which features interconnected characters and storylines.</p>
